programme.title: Boogeymen

programme.title: Boogeymen

programme.title: Ice Pilots: Gear Lock
programme.desc: A cold snap triggers massive challenges. Devan runs into gear problems while he ferries a mothballed DC-3 across the country. And Justin has to make a snap decision with his newborn son aboard his plane.

programme.title: Ice Pilots: Aussie Ace
programme.desc: The Electra returns from repairs and the crew takes it right back to the ice strip that it set off from before the crash landing last year. Tyler works up the courage to confront Joe about a big decision. A hotshot Australian pilot tries to earn a job.

programme.title: Ice Pilots: Rock Stars and Rampies
programme.desc: Facing Joe's wrath, Rod and Cory head to the UK to make urgent water bomber repairs. David tries to prove himself to Devan in the C-46 but ends up infuriating Devan. Will makes an ultimatum in Hay River.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Dark Signs, Part 3
programme.desc: With his life points on the line, Yusei confronts his former friend Kalin about their past in an effort to stop him from awakening the Army of Shadows.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Dark Signs, Part 4
programme.desc: The safety of the world hangs in the balance as Yusei tries to figure out a way to outduel and outmaneuver the unstoppable power of Kalin's dark deck.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Supersensory Shakedown
programme.desc: Leo is forced to take part in an extrasensory examination with the leader of the Arcadia Movement. Can Leo pass this pop quiz, or will this psychic showdown with Sayer leave Leo locked up forever?

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Digging Deeper, Part 1
programme.desc: With Lazar's creepy clowns about to crack Crow's defense, Crow hatches a plan to lull his opponent into a false sense of security so that his feathered friends can swoop in and swipe the last of Lazar's life points.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Digging Deeper, Part 2
programme.desc: Yusei gets caught up in a web of lies after agreeing to square off against Roman, the leader of the Dark Signers.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Digging Deeper, Part 3
programme.desc: With the safety of his friends literally hanging in the balance, Yusei must figure out a way to squash Roman's Earthbound Immortal before it sends him and his pals to the Netherworld forever.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Clash of the Dragons, Part 1
programme.desc: Luna gears up to face Devack in a Shadow Duel, but before the first card can be thrown, Luna is transported back to the Spirit World, leaving her pint-sized brother Leo the tall task of taking down this Dark Signer.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Clash of the Dragons, Part 2
programme.desc: As Luna searches the Spirit World for a way to free Ancient Fairy Dragon from her stone prison, Leo searches his deck for a card combo that will help him defeat Devack and his army of apes.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: The Signs of Time
programme.desc: Luna and her new found friend Torunka hatch a plan to free Regulus from King Zeman's minus curse. Meanwhile, back in the Satellite Sector, Leo calls upon his Power Tool Dragon to help him dismantle Devack's dark deck.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Surely, You Jest, Part 1
programme.desc: When Luna's plan to free Ancient Fairy Dragon falls apart, Regulus must come to her rescue in order to save her and the Spirit World from Zeman's minus curse.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Surely, You Jest, Part 2
programme.desc: Carly sets out hoping to uncover the mystery behind the Crimson Dragon, but after digging up some damaging dirt on the Arcadia Movement, she soon finds herself squaring off in a psychic duel with Sayer.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Mark of the Spider, Part 1
programme.desc: Sayer signs up for a Shadow Duel against a Dark Signer who's out for revenge while Akiza agrees to battle a dark and sinister supermodel.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Mark of the Spider, Part 2
programme.desc: As the Dark Signer double duel draws to a climactic close, Carly and Misty unfold a catastrophic card combo that could send Akiza and Sayer to the Netherworld forever.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Mark of the Monkey, Part 1
programme.desc: After Akiza falls into a state of unconsciousness, her father turns to Yusei in a last ditch effort to wake his beloved daughter from her catatonic condition.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Mark of the Monkey, Part 2
programme.desc: As the battle between Signers presses on, Yusei turns to his trusty Stardust Dragon in an effort to keep the power of Akiza's Black Rose Dragon at bay.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Mark of the Monkey, Part 3
programme.desc: With Yusei, Jack, Akiza and Luna all gathered together, Director Goodwin seizes the moment and decides to shed some light on the dark and formidable foes the four Signers will soon be battling.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Mark of the Monkey, Part 4
programme.desc: In an effort to rid the Satellite Sector of the Dark Signers, Crow ventures out and challenges a sinister looking sneak to a duel.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: A Whale of a Ride, Part 1
programme.desc: Crow challenges the newest member of the Dark Signers to a Turbo Duel, but before Crow's Blackwings can even take flight, his opponent unleashes an aerial assault of his own.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: A Whale of a Ride, Part 2
programme.desc: As the sky-high battle between Crow and Greiger heats up, Crow looks to elevate his game in order to ground Greiger's aerial attacks before they send him to the Netherworld forever.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: A Whale of a Ride, Part 3
programme.desc: With his life points on the line, Crow turns to his feathered friends in a last ditch effort to take out Greiger's Earthbound Immortal. Can Crow and his Blackwing's rise to the occasion?

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: A Score to Settle, Part 1
programme.desc: Haunted by the memories of his last battle with Kalin, Yusei looks to bury the past by agreeing to duel his former friend in a rematch. Can Yusei defeat Kalin and seal the tower that this Dark Signer is guarding?

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: A Score to Settle, Part 2
programme.desc: As the rematch between Kalin and Yusei continues, Yusei must find a way to out-think and out-maneuver the dark power of Kalin's Earthbound Immortal before it sends him to the Netherworld forever.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Destiny's Will, Part 1
programme.desc: Roman challenges Yusei to a Shadow Duel at the site of the original Ener-D Reactor. Meanwhile, Director Goodwin decides to make an unexpected visit to the Satellite Sector to settle some unfinished business he has with his Dark Signer brother.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Destiny's Will, Part 2
programme.desc: As the battle between Yusei and Roman rages on, Roman takes a time out to reveal the truth behind the original Ener-D Reactor's meltdown and the role Yusei's father played.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Shadows of Doubt, Part 1
programme.desc: Jack agrees to Turbo Duel Carly in an effort to defeat the darkness that has taken control of her. Can Jack rid the evil that has come to possess this one-time roving reporter?

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Shadows of Doubt, Part 2
programme.desc: Jack kicks his duel into overdrive and summons his Red Dragon Archfiend in a desperate attempt to free Carly from the Dark Signers' control.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Truth and Consequences, Part 1
programme.desc: Hoping to finally find out the whereabouts of her long-lost brother, Misty challenges Akiza to a Shadow Duel in a maze of mirrors.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Truth and Consequences, Part 2
programme.desc: After unlocking Akiza's psychic powers, Sayer sets his sights on using them to get even with the Dark Signers for destroying the Arcadia Movement.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Signs of Doom, Part 1
programme.desc: Yusei, Jack and Crow face off against Goodwin in the ultimate Shadow Duel showdown.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Signs of Doom, Part 2
programme.desc: With the safety of the world hanging in the balance, Yusei, Jack and Crow look to tip the scales in their favor by setting their sights on Goodwin's Earthbound Immortal.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Signs of Doom, Part 3
programme.desc: With his life points running on empty, Yusei looks to rev it up one last time in order to defeat Goodwin and save the world from the destructive powers of the King of the Netherworld!

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: A New Threat: Part I
programme.desc: A mysterious new threat arrives on the scene in New Domino City, forcing Yusei to take to the streets and track down a rogue Turbo Duelist known as The Ghost.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's
programme.desc: With his life points on the line, Yusei must figure out a way to take down Ghost's Meklord Emperor Wisel before Wisel's special ability throws his game and his runner into a tailspin.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Lessons Learned
programme.desc: When Vice Chancellor Rudolph Heitmann threatens to expel all the members of Leo and Luna's class from Duel Academy, Yusei attempts to teach the teacher a valuable lesson by challenging the Vice Chancellor to a duel to keep his friends in school.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Trash Talk
programme.desc: When Crow is asked to convince an old friend of Martha's to move into her retirement home, Crow decides to tackle the task by challenging the old man to a trash-talking junkyard duel. Can Crow convince the old man to relocate?

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: A Duel with Interest
programme.desc: When a loan shark starts sinking his teeth into New Domino City, Jack decides to reel in this money-grubbing menace for good by putting his most prized possessions on the line in a duel.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: The Wicked Spirits
programme.desc: When Leo and Luna decide to go exploring a nearby forest rumored to be haunted by wicked spirits, they soon discover that the rumors are all too real when a mysterious boy traps Luna in his house and challenges Leo to a duel.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: French Twist: Part I
programme.desc: Yusei wakes up to find himself trapped in the back of a big rig with a bump on his head and no way out. After a mysterious tip leads Akiza to Yusei's location, the two friends soon find themselves Turbo Dueling an unfamiliar foe.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: French Twist: Part II
programme.desc: As the battle between Yusei and Sherry races on, Sherry reveals some shocking secrets about the upcoming World Racing Grand Prix. Meanwhile, Akiza begins to gain a new understanding and appreciation for Turbo Dueling while riding shotgun to Yusei.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Synchro Straits
programme.desc: Before heading out to the event of the year - The World Racing Grand Prix Gala - Yusei challenges Jack to a Turbo Duel in the hopes of finding a new dueling strategy that doesn't involve the use of Synchro Monsters.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: The Synchro Solution
programme.desc: A mysterious duelist named Vizor offers to show Yusei a new dueling strategy known as The Synchro Solution.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Acceleration
programme.desc: Akiza goes to get her Turbo Dueling license, but before she can drive off into the sunset, she first has to out-duel, out-maneuver and out-smart one of Sector Security's finest for her final exam.

programme.title: All About the Money
programme.desc: Three try to capture United States' most wanted criminal and collect the $25 million bounty. Feat: Danny Trejo.

programme.title: Dead Heat
programme.desc: In this offbeat comedy thriller, Roger Mortis is a good cop who will do anything to nail the bad guys, even if he's got to die for it.

programme.title: Unlikely Hero
programme.desc: A washed-up writer forms an unlikely friendship with a teenager from Long Island. Starring: Jeff Daniels, Emma Stone, Ryan Reynolds, Lisa Kudrow, Kieran Culkin.

programme.title: Supernatural Activity
programme.desc: The world's most beloved illusionist, armed with his team, embarks on the most adventurous paranormal investigation of all time. Terrorised at every turn, this witch hunting, ghost busting.

programme.title: Moonwalkers
programme.desc: What if Apollo 11 never actually made it? What if, in reality, Stanley Kubrick secretly shot the famous images of the moon landing in a studio, working for the US administration? Feat Rupert Grint & Ron Perlman.

programme.title: Karaoke Man
programme.desc: When an introverted comic book illustrator discovers that the costume of an obscure Eastern European superhero supplies him with the courage to sing karaoke without fear, he uses his new-found voice to woo a cute waitress.

programme.title: Pirates of Treasure Island
programme.desc: An innkeeper's life of monotony suddenly changes when he comes into possession of a treasure map. Enlisting the help of Long John Silver and his band of cutthroat pirates, he sets off in search of the cursed Skeleton Island.

programme.title: Almighty Thor
programme.desc: When the demon god Loki destroys the fortress of Valhalla and steals the Hammer of Invincibility, only the young hero Thor can protect Earth from armageddon.

programme.title: Apocalypse Pompeii
programme.desc: When a Former Special Ops commando visits Pompeii, his family is trapped as Mt. Vesuvius erupts with massive force. While his family fights to survive, he enlists his former teammates in a daring operation beneath the ruins of Pompeii.

programme.title: Megafault
programme.desc: A seismologist and a miner must stop a massive earthquake that threatens to tear the world in half.

programme.title: Sherlock Holmes
programme.desc: Sir Arthur Conan Doyle's famous detective faces the ultimate challenge when enormous monsters attack London.

programme.title: Titanic II
programme.desc: On the 100th anniversary of the original voyage, a luxury liner follows the path of its namesake. But when a tsunami hurls an ice berg into the new ship's path, the passengers and crew must fight to avoid a similar fate.

programme.title: Snakes on a Train
programme.desc: Under a Mayan Curse, snakes are hatched inside a young woman, devouring her from within. With hours for her to live, she jumps on a train to Los Angeles to find a shaman, trapping the passengers aboard.

programme.title: Hillside Cannibals
programme.desc: The true story that inspired THE HILLS HAVE EYES of the reclusive Bean family who live in cliffside caves, attacking passerbys, taking their possessions and living off their flesh.

programme.title: Freakshow
programme.desc: When a gang of thieves hiding out in a circus sideshow decides to steal from the wealthy owner, there are horrific consequences!

programme.title: Born Bad
programme.desc: When a rebellious girl from a good family falls for the town drifter, she unwittingly brings a psychopath into her loving home.

programme.title: 666: The Child
programme.desc: After a plane crash where a boy is the only survivor, a childless couple adopts him and soon discovers he is something very powerful and very dark. This small boy is the Beast, and with him he carries the Beginning of the End.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: The House of The Devil
programme.desc: The island of Gran Canaria houses some of the most haunted buildings in the world and tonight the team fly to the island and investigate claims of satanic worship and paranormal activity in a house that is believed to have been built by the Devil himself.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: House of Fear
programme.desc: Located in Gran Canaria, there is one house that locals refuse to enter and that is, The House of Fear. Ghostly shadows, loud banging and demonic voices have all been reported here and the Ghost Dimension team will investigate these claims tonight.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension
programme.desc: Ghost Dimension investigate ruins of The Orangery in Merseyside and claims that the ghost of a grey lady is haunting the location. They capture some of the most compelling paranormal evidence they have ever encountered.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: What Haunts Inside?
programme.desc: Ghost Dimension is an exciting paranormal show that takes investigations to a whole new level.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: Halloween Special (2019)
programme.desc: Ghost Dimension is an exciting paranormal show that takes investigations to a whole new level.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo: The Curse Of The Pendle Witches - Part 1
programme.desc: Sean heads deep into the Pendle Hills in search of the Pendle Witches that went to trial in 1612 and were hung for witchcraft. The investigation takes an unexpected twist with a stop at the New Inn, Pendles most haunted pub.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo: The Curse Of The Pendle Witches - Part 2
programme.desc: Sean continues his investigation of Pendle Hill and ventures even deeper into the hills. The night takes an unexpected turn with a dramatic ending, which he believes was caused by the witches.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo: Shadow Menace Haunting Morley Market - Part 1
programme.desc: Sean heads to the town of Morley to investigate the infamous Morley Market. A place once bustling with people from years gone by, it is now haunted by shadow figures, and they appear to want to make themselves known.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo: Shadow Menace Haunting Morley Market - Part 2
programme.desc: Sean continues the investigation at Morley Market and appears to be followed by a spirit person that wants to touch him and distract him from investigating certain parts of the main hall. Will he uncover who this spirit is?

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo: Horror at Sandhole Cottage - Part 1
programme.desc: Sean returns to his former, haunted home. No tenant has ever been able to stay the full term. Sean wants to seek out the spirits once and for all, to finally find out what is haunting his former home.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo: Horror at Sandhole Cottage - Part 2
programme.desc: Sean continues his investigation of Sandhole Cottage and appears to be in direct contact with the spirits that haunted any tenants that came to live there. Will he finally get them to rest?

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo: Opening The Book at Leeds Library - Part 1
programme.desc: Sean delves deep and opens a new chapter for the Ghost Dimension Flying Solo series as he investigates Leeds Library, to uncover what is haunting and frightening the staff that work here.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo: Closing The Book at Leeds Library - Part 2
programme.desc: Sean continues his investigation at Leeds Library and attempts to communicate with a spirit known by the name of Sternberg. Will his investigation have a happy ending?

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo: Secret Spirits at The Old Market Tavern - Part 1
programme.desc: Sean heads to Altrincham, Greater Manchester to investigate The Old Market Tavern. Once used as a coaching inn and a court house, many spirits still lurk here and Sean captures one of the most clearest EVP's ever.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo: Secret Spirits at The Old Market Tavern - Part 2
programme.desc: Sean continues his paranormal investigation at The Old Market Tavern and he appears to have attracted the attention of spirit that launches a physical attack on him. Will he survive the night?

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo
programme.desc: Sean heads to Astley Green to the infamous Astley Green Colliery Museum. So many reports of paranormal activity have been confirmed at the mine, from lost miners to tormented souls.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo: Digging Deep Astley Green Colliery Museum - Part 2
programme.desc: Sean continues his investigation into Astley Green Colliery Museum and attempts to make further contact with the souls and spirits who have lost their lives there. Will he succeed?

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo: Historic Hauntings of Whittington Castle - Part 1
programme.desc: Sean heads to Oswestry to investigate claims of hauntings at a castle thousands of years old, and believed to be haunted by an angry judge. Will any of the souls that departed here come out to play?

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo: Historic Hauntings of Whittington Castle - Part 2
programme.desc: Sean continues his investigation of the castle and attempts to make contact with the spirit world. It appears he is not alone.

programme.title: Everyone Says I Love You
programme.desc: A New York girl sets her father up with a beautiful woman in a troubled marriage while her stepsister gets engaged. Starring: Woody Allen, Goldie Hawn, Julia Roberts, Edward Norton, Drew Barrymore, Natasha Lyonne, Natalie Portman.

programme.title: The Whole Wide World
programme.desc: Set in the 1930s, a Texas schoolteacher falls in love with pulp writer Robert H. Howard. The two couldn't be more opposite; sharing almost nothing, but their uniquely passionate romance.

programme.title: Jess + Moss
programme.desc: A series of vignettes involving memories of companionship and sexual awakening shared by two second cousins.\nThe film was selected for the Sundance and Berlin Film Festivals.

programme.title: From Nowhere
programme.desc: Nearing their high school graduation, three undocumented Bronx teenagers navigate the difficulties ofadolescence while living with the threat of being discovered by the authorities and their friends.

programme.title: The Missing Person
programme.desc: John Rosow is a private detective hired to tail a man who's gone missing only to discover that returning the man to his life may not be the best solution for the man, or himself. Starring: Michael Shannon, Frank Wood, Amy Ryan.

programme.title: Mary and Max
programme.desc: A tale of friendship between two unlikely pen pals: Mary, a lonely 8-year-old girl living in the suburbs of Melbourne and Max, a severely obese 44-year-old living in New York.

programme.title: The Last Time I Committed Suicide
programme.desc: Beat Poet Neal Cassady is pulled between two women, Mary, a teen temptress and J oan, his first true love. Starring: Thomas Jane, Keanu Reeves, Adrien Brody, John Doe, Claire Forlani.

programme.title: Burning Bodhi
programme.desc: Lifelong friends stumble back home after high school when word goes out on Facebook that the most popular among them has died. Old girlfriends, boyfriends, new lovers, parents, your first dead friend - how do people deal? Feat: Kaley Cuoco.

programme.title: Damage
programme.desc: A member of Parliament falls passionately in love with his son's fiancée despite the dangers of discovery. Starring: Jeremy Irons, Juliette Binoche, Miranda Richardson\nRichardson was nominated for an Academy Award and won a BAFTA.

programme.title: Jackals
programme.desc: From director Kevin Greutert of the SAW franchise comes a disturbing vision of a fractured family that will do anything to get the son they love back from the cult that has taken control of his mind. Feat: Stephen Dorff.

programme.title: Small Time Crooks
programme.desc: A loser of a crook and his wife strike it rich when a botched bank job's cover business becomes a spectacular success. Starring: Woody Allen, Tracey Ullman, Hugh Grant, Michael Rapaport, Tony Darrow, Laurine Towler.

programme.title: Popeye: New Adventures: Chips Off the Old Ice Block
programme.desc: Popeye and Bluto get into an argument over who will teach Swee'Pea to skate.

programme.title: Popeye: New Adventures: Shark Treatment
programme.desc: Popeye and Poopdeck Pappy go out to sea and they run across one of Poopdeck's old enemies from forty years back -- Monster Maki, the great white shark.

programme.title: Popeye: New Adventures: Mother Goose on the Loose
programme.desc: Popeye plans to tell his nephews some stories when Bluto interferes and wants to tell his own. Naturally, this leads to a disagreement form which Popeye emerges victorious.

programme.title: Popeye: New Adventures: A Camping We Will Go
programme.desc: Popeye's nephews persuade him to take them camping. At the camp site, his nephews eat all the food and then complain they are still hungry.

programme.title: Popeye: New Adventures: Take Me Out to the Brawl Game
programme.desc: Olive tries out for an all-male baseball team called the Burmingham Burgers.

programme.title: Popeye: New Adventures: Popeye Versus Machine
programme.desc: Both Popeye and Bluto want to win a contract, which will be given to the one who first finishes a 22-mile freeway through the mountains.

programme.title: Popeye: New Adventures: The Spinach Bowl
programme.desc: Once again Bluto and Popeye in fearce competition with each other. While Bluto's Bruisers take the lead in a tough football game with Popeye's Pouncers.

programme.title: Popeye: New Adventures: Ballet-Hooey
programme.desc: Bluto and Popeye are together in an argument because Bluto won't give Popeye his ball back. Their dispute interrupts Olive Oyl's ballet class and she insists they both stay in her class as dancers.

programme.title: Popeye: New Adventures: Yukon County Mountie
programme.desc: Popeye and Bluto volunteer to guard the payroll and do a special duty for the general which turns out to be having to shoe all the horses.

programme.title: Popeye: New Adventures: Queen of the Load
programme.desc: Popeye and Olive Oyl are partners driving a truck cross country. Bluto thinks he would do much better with his trucking business if he had Olive as a partner so he tries to talk her into it.

programme.title: Worst Cooks in America: Can It Really Be This Bad?

programme.title: Worst Cooks in America: Fish Are Food, Not Friends

programme.title: Worst Cooks in America: Show Me the Vegetables!
programme.desc: Boot camp is transformed into a game show, "Family Food," and the teams face off in trivia rounds and culinary tasks that test their knowledge.

programme.title: Worst Cooks in America: Game Day!
programme.desc: Recruits compete in cornhole and darts to determine flavors for their craveable game-day creations. For the main dish challenge, mentors Anne Burrell and Tyler Florence teach the recruits how to make irresistible stuffed burgers.

programme.title: Worst Cooks in America: Leftovers Again?
programme.desc: The recruits learn how to create new dishes from common leftover ingredients, then Anne and Tyler leave them alone for the first time to make pizza from scratch. Some pizzas impress the chefs, while others get boxed out.

programme.title: Worst Cooks in America
programme.desc: It's Valentine's Day at boot camp and the recruits are learning how to make molten chocolate cakes and multi-component desserts.

programme.title: Worst Cooks in America: Sausage Party
programme.desc: Anne and Tyler secretly watch the boot camp recruits as they learn the ugly truth of sausage making and present their dishes for a potluck dinner.

programme.title: Worst Cooks in America: Can You Please Pas-Ta Sauce
programme.desc: The recruits attempt to make pasta from scratch with a little help from Italian nonnas who have years of experience.

programme.title: Worst Cooks in America
programme.desc: The final four recruits compete to represent Anne and Tyler in the finale. First, they learn high-flying bartending tricks. Then, they must cook a dish and perform a flashy tableside demonstration for some very special guests.

programme.title: Worst Cooks in America: The Final Countdown
programme.desc: With coaching from Anne and Tyler, each of the final two recruits must cook a three-course meal for a panel of culinary experts. Judges Paulette Goto, Jordan Andino and Michael Chernow determine the $25,000 grand prize winner.

programme.title: Worst Cooks in America: Hit Me With Your Best Dish
programme.desc: A new cast of celebrity recruits arrives at boot camp to cook their signature dishes and learn how to make a classic breakfast.

programme.title: Worst Cooks in America: Mother Dough
programme.desc: Anne and Tyler watch their teams face off in a serious of food games. Later, the recruits must make their own unique pizzas.

programme.title: Worst Cooks in America: A La Cuisine!

programme.title: Worst Cooks in America: It's All for the Fans

programme.title: Worst Cooks in America: By Land and Sea

programme.title: Worst Cooks in America: Hibachi Heroes
programme.desc: After testing the recruits with a game of “Family Food,” Anne and Robert teach them how to make a hibachi-style meal for the main dish challenge.

programme.title: Worst Cooks in America
programme.desc: The contestants must work in teams to identify the ingredients of five “mother sauces” and create their own dishes for their chef. Later, the main dish challenge finds the chefs teaching their recruits to make fried chicken and cornbread.

programme.title: Worst Cooks in America: The Ick Factor
programme.desc: The kitchen can be a scary place, but the recruits must learn to face their fears in boot camp and are forced to expand their palates with some unusual ingredients.

programme.title: Worst Cooks in America: Piece of Cake
programme.desc: The recruits work in teams to recreate a dish by taste alone. Later, they must bake tiered cakes to suit two special guest judges: Gesine Prado and Jason Smith.

programme.title: Worst Cooks in America: Duck, Duck ...
programme.desc: The final four recruits start thinking about life after boot camp and learn to navigate a grocery store. Chefs Anne and Robert teach their ducklings how to make impressive duck two ways.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: While marriage is meant to be for life, it often ends in divorce. These wives took their marriages vow seriously: "till death do us part.".

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: These women never get their hands dirty: no blood touched them because they manipulate others to kill for them...but they didn't get away.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: Women who kill husbands, lovers, rivals and parents will shock society. But a very special horror is reserved for women who will kill their own.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: A lovely lady with an innocent smile, kind eyes, a charming personality? No one would suspect a woman like that would murder. These women don’t look or behave like killers.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: The heaviest judgments of convicted killers are reserved for those who committed premeditated murder. These women plot and plan. They know the consequences of their actions, but still they go forward to kill.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Under His Control
programme.desc: These are love stories with bleak, bloody endings. Blinded by desire, obsessed and malleable, some women fall into lethal relationships with dangerous, controlling men.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Secrets and Lies
programme.desc: Behind their friendly smiles, deadly women hide histories of bloodshed and murder.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Love Gone Wrong
programme.desc: Love can be beautiful, love can be blind and love can be deadly. Desire and jealousy are powerful forces driving women to dark and horrifying places in their minds.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Married to Murder
programme.desc: To the outside world, their marriages seemed happy. But behind closed doors, there was no domestic bliss. These women wanted out, but getting a divorce wasn’t their preferred option.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Teen Killers
programme.desc: They were too young to drink or vote but they were not too young to commit the most brutal of crimes. Some were driven by pure curiosity: how would it feel to take a life?

programme.title: Deadly Women: Love to Death
programme.desc: Love and money are a beautiful marriage, for the lucky ones they create a life of happiness and ease. Unless the love is of money, the bride is a killer, and the groom their victim.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Kill Their Own
programme.desc: A mother's most basic instinct is to protect her children, to put their needs above her own desire for money, freedom and men. But these deadly women break that sacred bond when they turn against that natural instinct and kill their own offspring.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: Revenge is one of the oldest motives for murder, but these cases are much more than an “eye for an eye.”.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: These deadly women were consumed by obsessions that overtook their minds and their lives. These women all had a fatal fixation.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Obsession
programme.desc: Deciphering what causes minds to corkscrew out of control is the complex work of the criminal profiler. Obsessions can take many forms: beauty, devotion, ego and power.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Hearts of Stone
programme.desc: Deadly Women are not always the ones you expect. They are not the strangers lurking in the dark, they are a young mother, a supportive wife and a grandmother - all killers. Behind their loving masquerade lies a wake of family horror and pain.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Greed
programme.desc: Known as “black widows,” these women kill their spouses, lovers and children for profit. Murder for them becomes a business. Their trade is murder. Their profit? Blood money.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: Crimes of revenge are usually single acts of passion. A brew of hatred and restitution boils over in a manic moment of fury. Once caught, revenge killers usually display remorse and atonement.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: No one doubts a woman’s capacity to love, but sometimes lust can turn lethal. In the ultimate fatal attraction, "Deadly Women" looks at cases of murder driven by obsessive love.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: A rifle in a shopping mall, a syringe of potassium chloride and a syringe of insulin, each in the hands of a mentally disturbed woman, lead to the tragic end of many lives.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: Judi Buenoano secretly murdered lovers to claim on insurance policies whilst nurse Genene Jones secretly killed at least 46 infants left in her care between 1980 and 1982.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Hunter's Game
programme.desc: In the 1970's and 80s, people went to Alaska looking for a fresh start, to reinvent themselves, or to disappear for a while. Some of those disappearances weren't by choice.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Dixie Mafia
programme.desc: On Mississippi's Gulf Coast, a Judge and his politician wife are murdered in their home. The killer left few clues. It looked like a professional hit, and the investigation led nowhere. But the FBI refused to give up.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Shattered Shield
programme.desc: In a city awash in narcotics the drug lords have all the power even over the police. Corruption in New Orleans grew like cancer, eating away at public safety and threatening to destroy the city. Crooked cops break the laws they were sworn to uphold.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Blood Brothers
programme.desc: When the small community of Noel, Missouri discovered their bank was robbed, they're shocked. When the bank president turned up missing, they're outraged. And when clues began to surface the facts were more terrible than anyone could have guessed.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Crime Spree
programme.desc: They swept through six states like a plague, thrill killers acting without rhyme or reason. They targeted adults and young girls, kidnapping, and murdering. And in their rampage, they left plenty of clues, but moving targets are the hardest to hit.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Family Secrets
programme.desc: A woman and her infant son vanish. The husband is frantic. The clues are scarce, but hopes linger, even as the hours and days tick by without a word. Was she on the run, or the victim of foul play?

programme.title: The FBI Files: Master Plan
programme.desc: Willow Springs, Illinois, seemed like any other quiet Midwestern community. But it was really one of the most corrupt places in the nation. This tiny village, nestled just outside of Chicago, was in the hip pocket of organized crime.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Firefight
programme.desc: In Miami, a gang of robbers targeted banks and armored cars. They carried assault weapons and weren't afraid to use them. They struck during the day, and sometimes twice a day. For awhile, they seemed unstoppable.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Killer Abroad
programme.desc: Beginning in 1990, Europe found itself in the clutches of a serial killer. He became an international outlaw, hopping from country to country to evade capture and to kill again.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Moving Target
programme.desc: When a sniper in Utah started targeting African-American men for death, authorities launched a massive investigation. With scant clues and no witnesses they found the odds stacked against them, and they had no idea where the killer would strike next.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Deadly Mission
programme.desc: When a family was murdered in Arkansas, it seemed like an isolated event. But soon the crime was revealed to be part of an ever-widening circle of violence that defined a new age of domestic terrorism.

programme.title: The FBI Files
programme.desc: In 1995, our nation's capital was also our nation's murder capital. Even the police weren't safe. While Washington, DC, law enforcement targeted criminals, the criminals targeted law enforcement, even gunning down officers on patrol.

programme.title: The FBI Files: .22 Caliber Killer
programme.desc: In Buffalo, New York, a sniper targeted African-American men. He held a city hostage, and threatened to ignite a racial powder keg. And it looked like others might be following his bloody example.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Driven to Kill
programme.desc: A serial rapist targeted women. His dark urges raged out of control and led him to murder. He followed a path so random it was impossible to trace, and all that tied him to his crimes were his access to the highways and a bizarre sexual fetish.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Deadly Obsession
programme.desc: Power is a responsibility as well as a privilege. But in the wrong hands, power can corrupt. For former Deputy Attorney General for the State of Delaware, losing sight of his sworn oath to uphold justice could prove lethal.

programme.title: The FBI Files: First and Kennedy Street Crew
programme.desc: In the early 1990's, Washington, D.C., became the murder capital of the nation. Few were left untouched by gang violence, which was ignited by the drug trade. By 1994, that violence would strike at the very heart of law enforcement.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Terror In Disguise
programme.desc: Banks use a variety of devices to discourage would-be robbers: security cameras, silent alarms, and exploding dye packs. But when an elusive bank robber targeted Seattle's banks, none of these precautions were effective.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Deadly Trail
programme.desc: The disappearance of young women triggered a search that spanned the Pacific Northwest. A massive media campaign failed to locate the drifter, who first charmed then killed them. As investigators followed his trail, he always stayed one step ahead.

programme.title: 1000 Waves to Surfing Glory
programme.desc: 1000 Waves to Surfing Glory is presented in a dream like structure with no distracting titles letting the visual imagery speak freely to your surfing soul and wanderlust.

programme.title: Chill: Crashed Ice Tour, Canada & Leo Slemett
programme.desc: Chill moves to the winter sports this week as we head to Niagara Falls, Canada where they are hosting the opening round of the Crashed Ice Tour.

programme.title: Chill: Wakeboarding Legend, Harley Clifford & Kiteboarding Elite, Liam Whaley
programme.desc: This week on CHILL we take a tour through one of the world's best board sports on the water with Harley Clifford. And we witness kiteboarding at its elite level with Spain's Liam Whaley and others.

programme.title: Chill: Cold Water Classic, Canada & World Cup Wakeboarding, Australia
programme.desc: Jarrad Howse takes Chill to the hidden surfing destination of Tofino in Canada. Cold, wet and windy but better yet, sublime surf! We catch up with the Pro's at the Cold Water Classic.

programme.title: Chill: World Cup Women's Waterski Jumping, Australia & World Cup Waterski Slalom, Indonesia
programme.desc: This week on Chill, it's water skiing around the world, we're at the jumping in Australia and the slalom in Palembang. We check out PKRA Mexico, then catch up with surfing sensations, Courtney Cologue and Sage Erickson.

programme.title: Chill: Swatch Girls Pro, France & Kite Foil Gold Cup, Mexico
programme.desc: Chill heads to France to follow some of the biggest names in women's Surfing for a day of relaxation. An inside look at the technique needed to perform at the highest level in Kitesurfing. And we Chill with Japanese surf star Izuku Tanaka.

programme.title: Chill: World Cup Wakeboarding, Indonesia & Longboard Pro Circuit, China
programme.desc: We look at the skills required and the thrills delivered by the wave that stands as the king of them all - the mighty Barrel. The Longboard Pro Circuit in China is our next destination where we hang out with Kassia Meador and Darcy Liu..

programme.title: Chill: Swatch Pro Tour, France & World Cup Waterski Jumping, Australia
programme.desc: Chill joins the girls of the Swatch Pro Tour in South West France, the top riders and local talent in the freestyle section of the PKRA event in Mexico and the men of world cup waterski jumping in Australia.

programme.title: Chill: World Cup Wakeboarding, Australia & Kitesurfing World Tour, Italy
programme.desc: The very best in Women's wakeboarding as the IWWF comes to Mandurah in Australia. The beautiful Italian Island of Sicily plays host to the Kitesurfing world Tour.

programme.title: Chill: Action Sports Game, Australia & Women's World Longboard Championship, China
programme.desc: Chill heads down under for some water ski-jumping with the Men's Action Tricks Comp and Women's Ski Jump. We take an in-depth look at the Women's longboard Championships in the South China Sea.

programme.title: Chill: Waterski Jump Legend, Freddy Krueger & Women Longboard Professionals, China
programme.desc: This week we will travel to Western Australia to catch up with the Waterski Jump Legend Freddy Krueger. Style, elegance and a hard edge of competition combine in China as we watch some of the best women longboard professionals.

programme.title: Chill: World Kitesurfing Champion, Youri Zoon
programme.desc: Chill heads to Rio to follow some of the biggest names in the Surfing arena. An inside look with World Kitesurfing Champion Youri Zoon and an intimate training session with a bunch of Wakeboarders.

programme.title: Chill: Freddy Krueger, Wakeboard World Cup Australia
programme.desc: Freddy "The Nightmare" Krueger is the undisputed ski jumping legend. Chill gets up close and personal to discover his drive and passion which ultimately keeps him striving for perfection.

programme.title: Chill: World Cup Wakeboarding, Australia & Kitesurfing World Tour, Morocco
programme.desc: We are on the waters of Mandurah, Australia for the men's finals at the IWWF Wakeboard World. Morocco is our next destination for the kitesurf world tour, and we profile Harley Clifford.

programme.title: Minds in the Water
programme.desc: The story of one surfer's international journey to help protect dolphins, whales and their ocean environment. Shot on location in Australia, the Galapagos, Chile and Japan, it captures a key moment in one person's life when apathy is no longer an option.

programme.desc: Tragedy unfolds at Westbrook Beach when lifeguards are unable to locate a missing man. The man will be deemed lost at sea if he isn’t found soon, so senior lifeguard Ant takes charge.

programme.title: Voyage of the Continents: Europe: Tropical Beginnings
programme.desc: One billion years ago there was just one great continent on earth. It began to break apart and Europe drifted away. Tectonic collisions, tropical vegetation, inland seas and hot lagoons are what temperate contemporary Europe is made of.

programme.title: Voyage of the Continents: Europe: A Turbulent Future
programme.desc: Over time, the Atlantic Ocean widened. Then Africa moved north, struck Europe and birthed the Alps. Erosion, volcanic activity, and ice ages fashioned an extraordinarily rich and varied continent, ready for the arrival of human beings.

programme.title: Voyage of the Continents: The Origins of Africa
programme.desc: Africa is Mother Earth. Gondwana, the first, single, landmass broke apart into today's continents, but its heart is Africa. Land of rifts, lakes and volcanoes, Africa's mineral deposits testify to its eons-old history.

programme.title: Voyage of the Continents: Africa Today
programme.desc: Volcanic activity and climate change define Africa's modern geological history. Recently meaning 50 million years ago the Arabian plate snapped off the African continent and joined Southeast Asia.

programme.title: Voyage of the Continents: North America
programme.desc: North America's physical features were formed by volcanic eruptions, earthquakes and an ice age. To understand the geological forces at play, we look at the Rockies, the Grand Canyon and Canadian Shield. Also - will part of California become an island?

programme.title: Voyage of the Continents: Central America
programme.desc: Central America takes us back to when the world was young. A fragile line of islands linking North and South America, the islands of the Caribbean are recent apparitions on earth and may not be here to stay.

programme.title: Voyage of the Continents: South America
programme.desc: One glance at a map of South America says it all: Andes and Amazonian basin. Two huge geological characteristics that describe how the continent came into being. The Amazon was once under the sea.

programme.title: Catalyst: Tattoos, Moon Mining, Muscle Fiber
programme.desc: Ruben Meerman delves deep into the science of tattoos, how do they stay in your skin, are they safe and how easy are they to remove?

programme.title: Catalyst: Friendship
programme.desc: Friendship. From before we can even speak, we seek the companionship of others. But why is this drive so powerful? And how come out of all the people we meet in our lives, we fall in friendship with some and not others?

programme.title: Catalyst: Wind, Birdstrike
programme.desc: Catalyst explores the power of the wind.

programme.title: Catalyst: Aircraft, Tilapia, Laser Danger
programme.desc: Military aircraft are increasingly being exposed to electromagnetic interference whether the source is natural, like lightning strikes, or human produced, like radars.

programme.title: Catalyst: Earth On Fire
programme.desc: In this Catalyst special, reporters Anja Taylor and Mark Horstman travel to opposite sides of the planet to find out.

programme.title: Catalyst: Lead Astray
programme.desc: Anja Taylor investigates current sources of lead exposure and its developmental effects on children.

programme.title: Catalyst: Tick Allergy & Alien Technology
programme.desc: This story is a must see if you want the latest tips on how best to remove a tick. Does the popular movie quote ET phone home' have any substance? But now there's a new way of looking for aliens.

programme.title: Catalyst: Powering The Mind
programme.desc: What is memory? In this episode Anja Taylor investigates how our memories change from childhood to adulthood and how we can build up greater brain reserves to power our mind into old age.

programme.title: Catalyst: Our Chemical Lives
programme.desc: Thousands of chemicals are used in everyday products in our water, our food and in the air we breathe. It's the chemical soup of modern life and it's virtually impossible to escape them.

programme.title: Update- The World in 50 Years: The Body
programme.desc: This episode concentrates on the future of the human body. The effect of medical progress on the body will dramatically change daily life, but this will be compounded by other technological innovations.

programme.title: Update- The World in 50 Years: The City
programme.desc: Infrastructures of large cities in the industrialized world are becoming difficult to manage. Technological trends in the coming decades will move towards a centralized management system to coordinate a city energy consumption, traffic and data networks.

programme.title: Update- The World in 50 Years: The World
programme.desc: Climate concerns, energy issues, peace and the race for weapons technology will dominate international headlines. We’ll take a scientific look at these topics to examine the future of nanotechnology and solar energy.

programme.title: James May's Man Lab
programme.desc: James shows how to disarm a WWII bomb, builds a concrete kitchen worktop, teaches the art of seduction in the style of Thomas Campion (1567 - 1620), learns how to polish a boot, builds a large scale model railway.

programme.title: James May's Man Lab
programme.desc: James shows how to build your own bar, navigate the seas using the powder of sympathy and a dog, how to duel with percussion pistols, stop running out of toilet paper and build an orchestra composed of grade 1 level musicians.

programme.title: James May's Man Lab

programme.title: Sabrina's Secret Life: Teacher's Pet

programme.title: Sabrina's Secret Life: I’m A Slave For Who?
programme.desc: Sabrina’s tired of sharing Harvey with all of his extra activities: sports practice, science club, after-school job at the local market, etc. But when she casts a spell making her Harvey’s top priority, she gets more than she planned on.

programme.title: Sabrina's Secret Life: Putting Off
programme.desc: Sabrina knows there’s a big assignment due at school - a term paper on a world conqueror. (She chose Attila the Hun, thinking he’d been given a raw deal by history; she’s going to tell the true story.

programme.title: Sabrina's Secret Life: Matchmaker Sabrina

programme.title: Sabrina's Secret Life: Green-Eyed Monster

programme.title: Sabrina's Secret Life: Lather, Rinse, Repent

programme.title: Sabrina's Secret Life: Food 'Tude
programme.desc: Sabrina is given cafeteria work for two weeks (all students rotate through). She’s cramming for a big test coming up in Ms.

programme.title: Sabrina's Secret Life: J’achoo
programme.desc: Down in the Netherworld, anticipation is building for a witch-specific holiday (like our Valentine’s Day or Halloween – like Mardi Gras, with everyone wearing masks).

programme.title: Sabrina's Secret Life: Just A Rumor
programme.desc: Using typical teenage bad judgment, Sabrina starts repeating a rumor she has heard from Tiffany & Margaux. It’s a fairly hurtful sort of rumor about one of their classmates.

programme.title: Sabrina's Secret Life: Pet Peeve
programme.desc: Sabrina wishes she had a pet. Oh, Salem’s okay as a pal, but as a loving furball, he doesn’t cut it.

programme.title: Sabrina's Secret Life: Best Of Show
programme.desc: There’s a dog show in Greendale. Cassandra has a stunning entry. Margaux and Tiffany are helping her train and show it.

programme.title: Sabrina's Secret Life: Here’s Looking At You
programme.desc: Sabrina agrees to help Maritza with her science project but oversleeps and forgets. At the witches’ academy, Sabrina and Cassandra meet a very frank magic mirror who insults and infuriates Cassandra.

programme.title: Sabrina's Secret Life: Hot Item
programme.desc: While shopping with Sabrina, Maritza ogles a necklace that Cassandra buys. Knowing how much Maritza wants it, the unkind young witch uses it to taunt Maritza.

programme.title: Sabrina's Secret Life: What’s In A Name?
programme.desc: Sabrina and Cassandra bicker their way through another potion-making assignment at the witches’ academy. Their arguing causes them to spill the entire vial of Salvia Muscaria: an extremely rare herb!

programme.title: Sabrina's Secret Life: Greendale Idol
programme.desc: At the witches’ academy, the Sabrina and Cassandra learn about the dangers of using magic carelessly.

programme.title: Sabrina's Secret Life: A Midsummer’s Nightmare
programme.desc: Shakespeare’s Puck leads us into this Bard-inspired story. and makes Sabrina the director.

programme.title: Sabrina's Secret Life: Cat Man Do
programme.desc: Salem is terrified to learn that the evil Toc-Toc is being released from suspended animation (a Netherworld corrections facility) for a crime Salem committed!

programme.title: Sabrina's Secret Life: Witchycology
programme.desc: Sabrina and Maritza unsuccessfully try to convince Cassandra that littering isn’t cool. The trash in Greendale is so bad, that these “best friends for life” get their favorite skateboard star, Ricky Speed, to come perform and clean up the pollution.

programme.title: Sabrina's Secret Life: Time Flies
programme.desc: Sabrina is excited when Maritza asks her to go to the Plain Brain concert, but when her aunts invite her on a trip to the hyper spa at the same time as the concert.

programme.title: Sabrina The Animated Series: Most Dangerous Witch
programme.desc: Tim the Witchsmeller is a disgruntled half witch who can perform no magic, and boy is he bitter.

programme.title: Sabrina The Animated Series: You Said a Mouse-Ful
programme.desc: Salem eats Sabrina's prize mouse for her science fair exhibit. After much blackmailing on Sabrina's part, she gets Salem to morph into a mouse to take its place.

programme.title: Sabrina The Animated Series: Boggie Shoes
programme.desc: Sabrina is psyched about school dance and can't understand why Harvey doesn't want to go.

programme.title: Sabrina The Animated Series: A Tail of Two Kitties
programme.desc: Salem falls for a fellow feline. He learns that she is a kittywitch as well. They fall in love and want to run off together.

programme.title: Sabrina The Animated Series: The Senses-Shattering Adventures of Captain Harvtastic
programme.desc: Harvey lacks the courage to show his comic book to the great comic book creator, King Kirby. Sabrina decides to give Harvey a Wishing Star in hopes that he'll wish for courage.

programme.title: Sabrina The Animated Series: Picture Perfect
programme.desc: The Student of the Year winner will be announced soon and Sabrina and Gem are tied to win. Gem uses her money to win the contest so Sabrina uses magic to make Gem lose.

programme.title: Sabrina The Animated Series: Field Trippin'
programme.desc: Sabrina, desperate to earn money for an upcoming concert, baby sits the terror twins. Hilda, Zelda and Uncle Quigley warn her that she's just not ready but Sabrina is adamant.

programme.title: Sabrina The Animated Series: No Time to Be a Hero

programme.title: Sabrina The Animated Series: Shrink to Fit

programme.title: Sabrina The Animated Series: Nothin' Says Lovin' Like Something From a Coven

programme.title: Sabrina The Animated Series: Wag the Witch

programme.title: Sabrina The Animated Series: Witchy Grrrls
programme.desc: Sabrina's band, the Flavor Babes, use a little magic to launch their careers. The much desired fame and riches end up tearing Sabrina, Chloe, Hilda and Zelda apart.

programme.title: Sabrina The Animated Series: Paranormal Pi

programme.title: Sabrina The Animated Series: Anywhere But Here
programme.desc: Sabrina is tired of the restrictions that come with being a kid. She casts a spell that catapults into adulthood.

programme.title: Sabrina The Animated Series: Documagicary

programme.title: 420 The Documentary
programme.desc: Scores of citizens attend 420 festivals to openly celebrate pot smoking, while others experience tragic consequences, such as citizens who've been arrested, shot and even murdered for mere possession of cannabis.

programme.title: Guardians of the New World: Guardians of the New World

programme.title: Food Evolution

programme.title: Royals and Animals: Til Death Do Us Part

programme.title: The Trick With The Gun

programme.title: Unsolved - The Story Of The Cape Ripper

programme.title: Whispers In The Dark

programme.title: Is She Or Isn't He

programme.title: Vulva 3.0: Between Taboo And Fine Tuning
programme.desc: “Showing the vulva scares off bears and lions, makes wheat grow higher, calms storm tides and demons fear it. The devil runs away. The vulva is omnipotent.” This powerful image of the female genitals is unfortunately not anchored in our imagination.

programme.title: Head First: Social Monster

programme.title: Head First: Fame, Lies And Sex Tape

programme.title: Space: The New Frontier: Atmosphere

programme.title: Space: The New Frontier: Flight Status

programme.title: Space: The New Frontier: Invasion Mars

programme.title: Space: The New Frontier: Juno, Cassini and Beyond

programme.title: Space: The New Frontier: Sling Shot
programme.desc: Soviet Luna 3 was the first to use gravity to change course to photograph the dark side of the Moon. NASA Mariner 10 used the technique to swing by Venus to target Mercury. The gravity sling shot maneuver has become a standard for space navigation.

programme.title: Space: The New Frontier: Living Planet
programme.desc: We have been observing Earth for 40 years now, in the last 20 we have focus with intensity on the planet with new technologies and capabilities, we have accumulated a mass of data that is now revealing a complex and ever changing living planet.

programme.title: Space: The New Frontier: Cosmic Collisions
programme.desc: Space is vast, yet it is full of collisions. Gas and dust electrostatically flock together, and gravity takes over coalescing grains into rocks. Those rocks become boulders, then asteroids colliding again and again, striking planets and each other.

programme.title: Space: The New Frontier: Gravity
programme.desc: Gravity keeps us on the ground and the planets in their orbits, yet we only notice it when it's not there. In space we cheat gravity; falling just as fast but missing the ground. Now this fundamental universal force is slowly giving up its secrets.

programme.title: Space: The New Frontier: Interface
programme.desc: The interface between Earth and space is the Ionosphere, a region of rarified gas and charged particles. It is very important for radio communications, radar, satellite signals and global positioning. Yet we know so little about it.

programme.title: The Amazing World of Gravity

programme.title: The Mystery of Dark Matter: The Mystery of Dark Matter
programme.desc: Dark matter, which is unknown and undetectable in our physical models, would appear to populate the cosmos on a massive scale. For the first time, a film portrays the wild scientific quest that dark matter gives rise to - a real thriller!

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Felons Interrupted
programme.desc: Dog is confronted with two alleged felons in crisis. Family and friends of these bondees are convinced that they are getting into further trouble while awaiting trial, so Dog and the posse have to bring these men back to jail.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Let It Snow
programme.desc: Christopher is barely 21, already has a history of domestic abuse and assault, and is facing major time in a room without a view. This hunt won't be easy for Dog - the leads are few, informers and family are not forthcoming.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Rush from Judgment
programme.desc: Facing hard time for forging checks, Melissa pulled a vanishing act at her sentencing hearing, bolting from the courthouse in broad daylight. Lucky for her bondsman, Dog and his posse are in Colorado and ready to help.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Burn & Return
programme.desc: Dog is busy. First, he's after a fugitive who is allegedly an expert in the game of "burn and return"- shoplifting goods to return them for cash refunds. But he's not easy to track.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Stormy Weather
programme.desc: Going after two fugitives in one day is tough enough without the facing Colorado's notoriously unpredictable weather. Today, it's the threat of severe thunderstorms, hail and area wide tornado warnings.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: One for the Money
programme.desc: It hurts Dog to see people who after years of walking the straight and narrow, suddenly lose their way. But today's case is a member of the law enforcement community who has recently gone astray, and that truly troubles the Dog.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Reality Check
programme.desc: Dog is back in Denver and in hot pursuit of a woman wanted for identity theft. The sad reality is that the identify which has been robbed is her own. She's traded in a bright future for a life on the wrong side of the law.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: No Piece of Cake
programme.desc: Being hunted by the Dog is a lousy way to celebrate your birthday but that's exactly the spot that Robert finds himself in today. He's missed his court date, quit his job, and vacated his last known address.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Prayers and Mace
programme.desc: Both brother Tim and fellow Honolulu bondsman James need Dog's help to track down their hard to find fugitives. The two cases on the docket today are challenging, especially the hunt for Gregory, a felon with a lengthy rap sheet.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: New Dog in Town
programme.desc: It's Beth's birthday and Dog knows just what she needs. He surprises Beth with Delilah, a puppy small enough to sit in the palm of her hand. Beth is so happy that she insists on taking the puppy with her on today's bounty.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Trick or Treat
programme.desc: It's Halloween, and before Dog and Beth can help the kids carve their pumpkins, they have some business to attend to. It involves knocking on doors and meeting the neighbors but instead of hunting for treats they're on the search for a fugitive.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Girl Trouble
programme.desc: Dog and the team have girl trouble in this case. Krystal jumped bail and seems to have vanished into the high plains of Colorado. To make matters worse, she's running with her lover (and bond co-signer) Carrie. But Thelma and Louise they ain't.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Seeing the Light
programme.desc: Today Leland and Dog make a quick visit to the police supply store to get some new gadgets for the team but they can't linger because they've also got a fugitive to catch. Their target is reputed to have an explosive temper.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: When a Stranger Calls
programme.desc: When an offender with a long record ducks his day in court, Bobby Brown knows whom to call - The Dog!? And knowing that few souls can resist Beth's clever persuasion, Dog gives her the job of luring the fugitive in.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Jack & Jill
programme.desc: Today's case is a twofer, a brother and sister both charged with drug related offenses. Also, Dog has crossed paths with the brother before. He once tried to stop Dog from arresting one of the most violent fugitives of his career.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Island Hopper
programme.desc: When a brother bondsman from Washington State calls Dog for help tracking a runner in search of fun in the sun on the tropical paradise of Kauai, the team gets on the case. Dog's only problem? No leads!

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Nice Guys Finish Last
programme.desc: Dog and team help out a bondsman friend whose client jumped bail, but the target is a blank slate. Are his tattoos gang related? Is he likely to be violent? And making matters worse, when they hit his apartment they learn he is moving out.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Back Behind Bars
programme.desc: While tracking down a potentially dangerous ex-con facing a five year stretch in the big house, Leland struggles to find time to train and compete for his first boxing match in years.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Family Man
programme.desc: Dog and family head to Kona to track down a wanted father who's looking to bolt to the mainland to evade sentencing. Meanwhile, Dog does some evading of his own - Avoiding the much dreaded birthday party!

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: All in the Family
programme.desc: Dog and the team need to help Leland hunt down some elusive fugitives. The case is a family affair with both mother and daughter in trouble with the law.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Mother Courage
programme.desc: Dog knows that crime and drugs not only damage victims but also harm the families of the perpetrators, especially the kids. And both of the fugitives he's chasing today have left shattered families and struggling women in their wake.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Bounty Boot Camp
programme.desc: Jim is a bondsman and longtime friend of Dog. Jim's son has just started in the family business. Today, Jim has asked Dog to track down a potentially dangerous fugitive, and take his son along for some training with the best in the world.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Friends and Neighbors
programme.desc: Dog and his posse head to Colorado for a special mission, to catch Marco, an alleged drug dealer. It's been ten months since Marco went on the lam, and his bondsman stands to lose his family business if Marco is not caught.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: The Set-Up
programme.desc: The trail is hot and the stakes is high for Dog and the posse. The "Big Fish" in this case is Marco, an alleged drug dealer with a big bond. But a major key to catching him is Elizabeth, who is also a fugitive from the law.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: The Searchers
programme.desc: Dog is still on the search for the elusive fugitive, Marco. Dog has been tracking him across Colorado, from Grand Junction to Denver, and now a hot tip that a long time associate of his is hiding in Pueblo sends the team racing south.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Buddha's Delight
programme.desc: Dog and the posse travel to the Big Island to help Leland track down a small-time Bonnie and Clyde couple. Their crime: theft, including allegedly stealing a pair of Buddha statues for resale.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Three's Company
programme.desc: This fugitive is hard to pin down in Honolulu's downtown district, moving from hostel to hotel to apartment high-rise. But as the hunt evolves, Dog discovers that this alleged burglar isn't the only family member wanted by the law.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Strip Search
programme.desc: When a stripper goes on the lam, Dog has to bring her in. It's a tough job but somebody has to do it. Thankfully for the team, Lady Luck is presiding over the posse tonight.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Secret Places
programme.desc: When Leland learns that one of his clients with a reputation for stealing has lost her co-signer and could be ready to run, Dog and the crew hop a plane to the Big Island.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Wrong Turn
programme.desc: Dog's target today seems to have a taste for drugs and a record of reckless driving. The hunt has deep emotional resonance for the team because today is the anniversary of the fatal car accident of Dog's daughter Barbara Katie.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Easy Rider
programme.desc: What looks like a routine pick-up turns into a complicated case of betrayal, deceit, as well as quality nail care as Dog and company track down a fugitive alleged to be an abusive boyfriend with one too many friends in his close knit community.
